qas.question: Most major airports provide commercial outlets for what?
Where are most of these companies located in an airport?
Some of these companies include what type of businesses?
Are prices at these outlets generally higher or lower than street prices?

plausible_answers.text: commercial outlets for products and services

qas.question: What do restaurants do to keep prices low?

plausible_answers.text: regulate costs to keep them comparable to "street prices"

qas.question: What does boutique management do to make sure their prices aren't too high?
How much are items outside of the aiport compared to discounted prices at boutiques inside the airport?
Where are companies with discounted prices located in an airport?
